        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 10 at 3:39PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 338 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Dakota, or 9 miles northeast of Freeport, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Harrison, Shirland, Lake Summerset, Durand, Rockton, and South
Beloit.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
